{
  "$comment": [
    "Resource-type allowlist for importer/kit discovery — the DATA the kit's scripts run on.",
    "Derived from the two things this repo already supports: (a) the resource types the prod",
    "import actually adopted (importer/prod/imports.tf — 76 types; every `id` shape below is",
    "verified against a real block in that archive) and (b) the types the Cloud Control Plane catalog",
    "manages (ccp/app/src/data/manifests/*.json resourceTypes).",
    "",
    "TO EXTEND: add an entry under `types` (schema below), author a fixture capture under",
    "testdata/, and add a test. Types that cannot be enumerated with ONE list call belong in",
    "`manual` instead — they are copied verbatim into every discovery manifest as",
    "manual_followup so they are never silently absent (0007 silent-loss lesson).",
    "",
    "Entry schema (types):",
    "  service   file/service name the resource lands in (mirrors environments/prod/<service>.tf)",
    "  arnHint   the ARN service-namespace token (arn:partition:SERVICE:region:account:resource)",
    "            this type's resources appear under. Used ONLY by discover.py's coverage sweep",
    "            (an `aws resourcegroupstaggingapi get-resources` capture, discover.sh 'Gap 1')",
    "            to bucket every swept ARN into covered/manual/unrecognized. Deliberately coarser",
    "            than the Terraform type: one AWS service namespace often maps many types here",
    "            (e.g. ec2 covers vpc/subnet/security_group/instance/volume/...), so the sweep",
    "            catches a wholly NEW service showing up in the account, not a new resource type",
    "            within an already-covered service — see importer/kit/README.md 'coverage sweep'",
    "            for that stated limit. Required (validated like the keys below); usually equals",
    "            the `cli` command's service token, EXCEPT where AWS's ARN namespace diverges from",
    "            the CLI service name (efs -> elasticfilesystem, elbv2 -> elasticloadbalancing) —",
    "            verified per type against real AWS ARN formats, not derived mechanically.",
    "  capture   basename (no .json) of the recorded CLI output in the capture dir",
    "  cli       the exact read-only AWS CLI command discover.sh runs to produce that capture",
    "  records   dotted path into the capture JSON; a trailing [] flattens a list;",
    "            '.' means the document itself. Records may be objects or plain strings.",
    "  id        field path on a record ('.' = the record itself) OR use id_format",
    "  id_format python str.format template over record fields, e.g. {Device}:{VolumeId}:{InstanceId}",
    "  name      display-name resolution: a path, 'tag:<Key>' (Tags list or map), or a",
    "            fallback LIST of those. Final fallback is always the id.",
    "  skips     [{field, prefix|equals, reason}] — matching records go to manifest.ignored",
    "            WITH the reason, never dropped silently",
    "  phase     importer/docs/strategy.md phase (2 low-risk · 3 networking · 4 compute · 5 stateful)",
    "  stateful  true ⇒ normalize.py `guard` inserts lifecycle { prevent_destroy = true }",
    "            (strategy.md rule 2: guards go in BEFORE import)",
    "",
    "Entry schema (manual[] groups) additionally carries:",
    "  arnHints  list of ARN service-namespace tokens this group's types are confidently known to",
    "            appear under (may be [] when the group's types are sub-resources with no ARN of",
    "            their own, e.g. S3 bucket configs, IAM inline policies/attachments). A long-tail",
    "            type whose exact ARN token is NOT independently verified is left out on purpose —",
    "            it will surface as an unrecognized coverage-sweep family rather than a guessed,",
    "            possibly-wrong mapping (honest gap over a silent one, same rule as everywhere else",
    "            in this file)."
  ],
